context: <a0_0><b5_0>India<b5_0/><a0_0/> started the construction of a 40,000-tonne, 260-metre-long (850 ft) Vikrant-class aircraft carrier in 2009. The new carrier will operate MiG-29K and naval HAL Tejas aircraft along with the Indian-made helicopter HAL Dhruv. The ship will be powered by <a1_0><b6_0>four gas-turbine engines<b6_0/><a1_0/> and will have a range of <a2_0><b7_0>8,000 nautical miles<b7_0/><a2_0/> (15,000 kilometres), carrying 160 officers, 1,400 sailors, and 30 aircraft. The carrier is being constructed by <a3_0><b8_0>Cochin Shipyard<b8_0/><a3_0/>. The ship was launched in <a4_0><b9_0>August 2013<b9_0/><a4_0/> and is scheduled for commissioning in 2018.
